data.title: 1965 Wimbledon Championships - Men's Singles
data.meta_description: 1965 Wimbledon Championships – Men's Singles  - Free download as PDF File (.pdf), Text File (.txt) or read online for free. Roy Emerson successfully defended his title at the 1965 Wimbledon Championships, defeating Fred Stolle in the final 6–2, 6–4, 6–4. The top seeds were Roy Emerson (1) and Fred Stolle (2). The draw consisted of 128 players, including 10 qualifiers, with Roy Emerson defeating opponents like John Cooper and Jim McManus to reach the final against Fred Stolle.
